145: SPSS was originally developed by Stanford University students Norman H. Nie, C. Hadlai "Tex" Hull, and Dale H. Bent in 1968. The software was later commercialized by SPSS Inc., which was founded in 1968 by Stanford students and faculty. The company was acquired by IBM in 2009, after which the software became known as IBM SPSS Statistics.
